div.font:
The server interface has constraints and limits. No client should appear to break these rules. Note that it should be
sufficient for the client to respect the return values of various API calls (although if it isn’t the client must not break a rule).
• Tank can move once in every X seconds. (X = 0.5);
• Tank can fire once in every Y seconds. (Y = 0.5);
•
• Tank can make only one turn per step. (E.g., Correct turn: NORTH -> WEST Incorrect turn: NORTH -> SOUTH);
• Tank can only move forward or back relative to its current direction. No sideways movements are allowed.
Start in InMemoryGameRepo in the turn method
The turn method then calls getTanks and gets the tank id to find the right tank
it then checks if the tank exists ? if it does it carries on : if not it throws a tankdoesnotexist exception.
Next it gets the systems current time in milliseoncds and
then calls on Game.getlastMoveTime() to see if it is less than the current milliseoncs if the tanks last move time is less false is returned
